\f0\b\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 Tables in HTML Emails\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl330\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 Understanding tables is essential for creating layouts in HTML emails. They can be used to create columns and adjust the spacing of content.\cb1 \
\cb3 Tables can be modified with inline CSS styles; however, it's often preferable to modify them with HTML attributes.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Some of the main attributes to modify tables are: border, cellpadding (the HTML attribute equivalent of box-model padding), and cellspacing (the HTML attribute equivalent of box-model margin).\cb1 \
